Implement SQLAlchemy-style event hooks for models.

## Event Types

### Instance Events
- before_insert - Before INSERT executed
- after_insert - After INSERT executed
- before_update - Before UPDATE executed
- after_update - After UPDATE executed
- before_delete - Before DELETE executed
- after_delete - After DELETE executed
- load - After loading from database
- refresh - After refresh from database

### Attribute Events
- set - When attribute value changes
- append - When item added to collection
- remove - When item removed from collection

### Session Events
- before_flush - Before flush begins
- after_flush - After flush completes
- before_commit - Before commit
- after_commit - After commit
- after_rollback - After rollback

## Rust Implementation

Use traits and callbacks:
```rust
pub trait ModelEvents {
    fn before_insert(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_insert(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn before_update(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_update(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn before_delete(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_delete(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
}
```

Or use attribute-based hooks:
```rust
#[derive(Model)]
struct User {
    #[sqlmodel(on_insert = "hash_password")]
    password: String,
}
```

